# BLOCKING since Run F2 (OQ-13/OQ-11): flipped on when coordinator/transport/ landed; scope EXTENDED to
# core/ in Run F3 (FLAG-F) after the 5 performance-enum-size findings were cleared (explicit underlying
# type on each core/ enum). Scoped to the framework-free hand-written logic (core/ + transport/proto/)
# via the Makefile's TIDY_FILES + the HeaderFilterRegex below — the core/ enums live in HEADERS, so the
# regex MUST cover core/ for the check to fire. transport/vendor/ (Victor's reference source), the
# Arduino-coupled transport/hw/, and the framework-coupled ui/ (TFT_eSPI) are NOT linted (blanket tidy
# over framework code is noise).
#
# bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters is disabled: it fires on ordinary multi-string/int signatures
# (telnet_run, build_write_file_cmd, …) and is widely treated as noise, not a real-bug signal.
Checks: >
  clang-analyzer-*,
  bugprone-*,
  performance-*,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters
WarningsAsErrors: 'clang-analyzer-*,bugprone-*,performance-*'
HeaderFilterRegex: 'firmware/coordinator/(core|transport/proto)/.*'
